<inglise> Article 8 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 8 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> After ceasing to hold office, members of the Commission or of the Court shall be entitled to a pension for life payable from the date when they reached the age of sixty-five years. </inglise>
<eesti> P&auml;rast ametist lahkumist saavad komisjoni ja Euroopa Kohtu liikmed eluaegset pensioni, mida makstakse alates p&auml;evast, mil nad saavad 65aastaseks. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 9 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 9 </eesti>
<inglise> The amount of the pension shall be 4.5 % of the basic salary last received for each full year in office and one-twelfth of that sum for each complete month. </inglise>
<eesti> Pensioni suurus on 4,5% viimati saadud p&otilde;hipalgast iga t&ouml;&ouml;tatud t&auml;isaasta eest ning 1/12 nimetatud summast iga t&auml;iskuu eest. </eesti>
<inglise> The maximum pension shall be 50 % of the basic salary last received. </inglise>
<eesti> Maksimumpension on 50% viimati saadud p&otilde;hipalgast. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 10 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 10 </eesti>
<inglise> A member of the Commission or of the Court who is suffering from disablement deemed to be total which prevents him from performing his duties and who on these grounds resigns or is compelled to resign shall be entitled from the date of resignation or compulsory resignation to the following benefits; </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjoni v&otilde;i Euroopa Kohtu liige, kes on p&uuml;sivalt t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetu ega saa seep&auml;rast oma &uuml;lesandeid t&auml;ita ning ametist lahkub v&otilde;i tagandatakse, saab tagasiastumise v&otilde;i tagandamise kuup&auml;evast alates j&auml;rgmisi toetusi: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) where disablement is recognised as permanent, he shall be entitled to a pension for life calculated in accordance with the provisions of Article 9, which shall be not less than 25 % of the basic salary last received. </inglise>
<eesti> a) p&uuml;siva t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse korral eluaegse pensioni, mida arvutatakse artikli 9 kohaselt ning mis peab olema v&auml;hemalt 25% viimati saadud p&otilde;hipalgast. </eesti>
<inglise> He shall be entitled to the maximum pension if the incapacity is the result of disablement or illness contracted in the performance of his duties; </inglise>
<eesti> Juhul, kui t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse p&otilde;hjustab t&ouml;&ouml;kohustuste t&auml;itmisest tingitud haigus v&otilde;i invaliidsus, on tal &otilde;igus saada maksimumpensioni; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) where disablement is temporary, he shall be entitled, until he recovers, to a pension at the rate of 50 % of the basic salary last received, if the disablement or illness was contracted in the performance of his duties, and 25 % in other cases. </inglise>
<eesti> b) ajutise t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse korral saab ta t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;ime taastumiseni pensioni, mis on viimati saadud p&otilde;hipalgast t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisest tingitud t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse v&otilde;i haiguse korral 50% ning muudel juhtudel 25%. </eesti>
<inglise> When the recipient of such disability pension reaches the age of sixty-five years or the disability pension has been in effect for seven years it shall be replaced by a pension for life calculated in accordance with the provisions of Article 9. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui nimetatud invaliidsuspensioni saaja saab 65aastaseks v&otilde;i kui invaliidsuspensioni on makstud seitse aastat, asendatakse see eluaegse pensioniga, mis arvutatakse artikli 9 kohaselt. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 11 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 11 </eesti>
<inglise> A member of the Commission or of the Court shall be entitled to the benefits of the social security scheme provided for in the staff regulations of oficials of the European Communities covering sickness, occupational disease, industrial accident and birth and death benefits. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjoni v&otilde;i Euroopa Kohtu liige saab Euroopa &uuml;henduste ametnike personalieeskirjadega etten&auml;htud sotsiaalkindlustusskeemi kohaseid toetusi haiguse, kutsehaiguse ja t&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;nnetuse korral, lapse s&uuml;nnitoetust ja matusetoetust. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 12 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 12 </eesti>
<inglise> Where a third party is responsible for the disablement or death of a member, the rights of that member or those entitled under him to bring legal proceedings against the third party shall devolve on the Community to the extent to which they incur obligations under this pension scheme. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui liikme t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuses v&otilde;i surmas on s&uuml;&uuml;di kolmas isik, l&auml;hevad selle liikme v&otilde;i tema p&auml;rijate &otilde;igused algatada nimetatud kolmanda poole suhtes kohtumenetlus &uuml;le &uuml;hendusele liikme pensioniskeemiga seotud kohustuste ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 13 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 13 </eesti>
<inglise> The transitional allowance provided for in Article 7, the pension provided for in Article 8 and the pensions provided for in Article 10 shall not be drawn concurrently by the same person. </inglise>
<eesti> Artiklis 7 s&auml;testatud &uuml;leminekutoetust, artiklis 8 s&auml;testatud pensioni ja artiklis 10 s&auml;testatud pensione ei maksta &uuml;hele isikule &uuml;heaegselt. </eesti>
<inglise> Where a member of the Commission or of the Court is entitled to claim benefit under more than one of those provisions, only that provision which is the most favourable to the claimant shall be applied. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui komisjoni v&otilde;i Euroopa Kohtu liige on &otilde;igustatud toetust v&otilde;i pensioni saama rohkem kui &uuml;he loetletud s&auml;tte kohaselt, kohaldatakse &uuml;ksnes saaja jaoks soodsaimat s&auml;tet. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 14 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 14 </eesti>
<inglise> Where a member of the Commission or Court dies during his term of office, the surviving spouse or dependent children shall be entitled, until the end of the third month following that in which death occurrs, to the remuneration to which the member of the Commission or of the Court would have been entitled under Articles 2, 3 and 4 (1). </inglise>
<eesti> Kui komisjoni v&otilde;i Euroopa Kohtu liige ametiaja jooksul sureb, saavad tema lesk ja &uuml;lalpeetavad lapsed surmale j&auml;rgneva kolmanda kuu l&otilde;puni t&ouml;&ouml;tasusid, mida komisjoni v&otilde;i Euroopa Kohtu liige pidanuks saama artiklite 2, 3 ja artikli 4 l&otilde;ike 1 kohaselt. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 15 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 15 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The widow and dependent children of a member or former member of the Commission or of the Court to whom pension rights have accrued at the time of his death shall be entitled to a survivor's pension. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjoni v&otilde;i Euroopa Kohtu sellise liikme v&otilde;i endise liikme lesk ja &uuml;lalpeetavad lapsed, kellel oli surma ajal &otilde;igus saada pensioni, saavad toitjakaotuspensioni. </eesti>
<inglise> That pension shall be equal to a percentage of the pension accruing to the member or former member of the Commission or of the Court under Article 9 at the date of death, namely: For a widow 50 % </inglise>
<eesti> Nimetatud pension moodustab komisjoni v&otilde;i Euroopa Kohtu liikmele v&otilde;i endisele liikmele surma ajal artikli 9 kohaselt maksmisele kuulunud pensionist j&auml;rgmise protsendi: </eesti>
<inglise> For each child where both father and mother are dead 20 % However, if the death of the member of the Commission or of the Court occurs during his term of office, the survivor's pension shall be calculated on the basis of a pension equal to 50 % of the basic salary received at the time of death. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui komisjoni v&otilde;i Euroopa Kohtu liige sureb oma ametiaja jooksul, on toitjakaotuspensioni arvutamise aluseks 50% tema surmaaegsest p&otilde;hipalgast. </eesti>
<inglise> Where the member of the Commission or of the Court whose death occurs during his term of office has reached the maximum pension provided for in Article 9, the survivor's pension for the widow shall be equal to 30 % of the basic salary received at the time of death. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui komisjoni v&otilde;i Euroopa Kohtu sellise liikme pension, kes suri oma ametiaja jooksul, oli j&otilde;udnud artiklis 9 s&auml;testatud maksimumpensionini, on lesele makstav toitjakaotuspension 30% tema surmaaegsest p&otilde;hipalgast. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The total amount of these survivors' pensions shall not exceed the amount of the pension of the member or former member of the Commission or of the Court on which they are calculated. </inglise>
<eesti> Toitjakaotuspensionide kogusumma ei tohi &uuml;letada komisjoni v&otilde;i Euroopa Kohtu liikme v&otilde;i endise liikme pensioni, mille alusel neid arvutatakse. </eesti>
<inglise> The maximum total survivors' pensions payable shall be divided, where applicable, between the beneficiaries in accordance with the above percentages. </inglise>
<eesti> Vajaduse korral jaotatakse maksimaalsed toitjakaotuspensionid pensionisaajate vahel eespool nimetatud protsentide kohaselt. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Survivors' pensions shall be granted from the first day of the calendar month following the date of death; however, where the provisions of Article 14 are applied, eligibility shall not commence until the first day of the fourth month following that in which death occurred. </inglise>
<eesti> Toitjakaotuspensione makstakse alates surmale j&auml;rgneva kuu esimesest p&auml;evast; kui kohaldatakse artikli 14 s&auml;tteid, tekib &otilde;igus pensioni saada surmale j&auml;rgneva neljanda kuu esimesel p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> Entitlement to a survivor's pension shall cease at the end of the calendar month in which the person entitled dies. </inglise>
<eesti> &Otilde;igus toitjakaotuspensioni saada l&otilde;peb selle kalendrikuu l&otilde;pus, mil &otilde;igustatud isik sureb. </eesti>
<inglise> Moreover, entitlement to an orphan's pension shall cease at the end of the month in which the child reaches the age of twenty-one years. </inglise>
<eesti> &Otilde;igus orvupensioni saada l&otilde;peb selle kuu l&otilde;pus, mil laps saab 21aastaseks. </eesti>
<inglise> However, entitlement shall be extended while the child is receiving vocational training, though not beyond the end of the month in which he reaches the age of twenty-five years. </inglise>
<eesti> Pensioni saamise &otilde;igust v&otilde;ib siiski pikendada, kui laps omandab kutseharidust, kuid mitte kauem, kui tema 25aastaseks saamise kuu l&otilde;puni. </eesti>
<inglise> The pension shall remain payable to an orphan who is prevented through illness or disablement from earning a livelihood. </inglise>
<eesti> Orvule, kes haiguse v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse t&otilde;ttu ei suuda elatist teenida, makstakse pensioni edasi. </eesti>
<inglise> 5. </inglise>
<eesti> 5. </eesti>
<inglise> Where a former member of the Commission or of the Court marries and at the date of marriage has pension rights accruing to him under this regulation, the wife and any children of the marriage shall not be entitled to a survivor's pension save where the marriage precedes the death of the former member of the Commission or of the Court by five years or more. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui komisjoni v&otilde;i Euroopa Kohtu endine liige abiellub ning on abiellumise kuup&auml;eval k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse kohaselt pensioni&otilde;iguslik, ei saa abikaasa ja abielupaari lapsed toitjakaotuspensioni, kui abielu oli komisjoni v&otilde;i Euroopa Kohtu liikme surma ajaks kestnud v&auml;hem kui viis aastat. </eesti>
<inglise> 6. </inglise>
<eesti> 6. </eesti>
<inglise> A widow's entitlement to a survivor's pension shall cease on remarriage. </inglise>
<eesti> Lese &otilde;igus saada toitjakaotuspensioni l&otilde;peb taasabiellumise korral. </eesti>
<inglise> She shall then be entitled to immediate payment of a lump sum equal to twice the annual amount of her survivor's pension. </inglise>
<eesti> Sellisel juhul makstakse talle viivitamata &uuml;hekordne toetus kahe aasta toitjakaotuspensioni suuruses summas. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 16 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 16 </eesti>
<inglise> A member of the Commission or of the Court who is relieved of his duties on grounds of serious misconduct shall forfeit any right to transitional allowance and retirement pension; this shall not, however, affect those entitled under him. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjoni v&otilde;i Euroopa Kohtu liige, kes vabastatakse ametist raske &uuml;leastumise t&otilde;ttu, kaotab &otilde;iguse saada &uuml;leminekutoetust ja vanaduspensioni; see ei m&otilde;juta siiski tema kaudu &otilde;igustatud isikuid. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 17 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 17 </eesti>
<inglise> Should the Council decide to increase the basic salary, it shall at the same time decide on an appropriate increase in the rates of existing pensions. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui n&otilde;ukogu otsustab p&otilde;hipalka t&otilde;sta, teeb ta samal ajal otsuse ka olemasolevate pensionide kohase t&otilde;stmise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 18 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 18 </eesti>
<inglise> Payment of the benefits provided for in this pension scheme shall be entered in the budget of the Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva pensioniskeemi kohaselt maksmisele kuuluvad summad kavandatakse &uuml;henduste eelarvesse. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall jointly guarantee payment of these benefits in accordance with the scale for financing such expenditure. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid tagavad &uuml;hiselt nimetatud toetuste maksmise vastavalt nimetatud kulude rahastamise ulatusele. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 19 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 19 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Payment of the sums due under Articles 2, 3, 4, 5, 11 and 14 shall be made in the currency of the country where the institution has its provisional seat. </inglise>
<eesti> Artiklite 2, 3, 4, 5, 11 ja 14 kohased summad makstakse v&auml;lja selle riigi v&auml;&auml;ringus, kus institutsioon ajutiselt asub. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Beneficiaries may elect to have sums due under Articles 7, 8, 10 and 15 paid in the currency either of the country of which they are nationals or of their country of residence or of the country where the institution which they serve has its provisional seat; their choice shall remain operative for at least two years. </inglise>
<eesti> Tulusaajad v&otilde;ivad lasta artiklite 7, 8, 10 ja 15 kohased summad maksta selle riigi v&auml;&auml;ringus, mille kodanikud nad on, oma elukohariigi v&auml;&auml;ringus v&otilde;i selle institutsiooni ajutise asukohariigi v&auml;&auml;ringus, kelle teenistuses nad on; valik kehtib v&auml;hemalt kaks aastat. </eesti>
<inglise> Where neither the first nor the second of these countries is a member country of the Community the sums due shall be paid in the currency of the country where the institution by which they were employed has its provisional seat. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui osutatud riikidest esimesed kaks ei ole &uuml;henduse liikmesriigid, makstakse summad selle riigi v&auml;&auml;ringus, kus asub ajutiselt institutsioon, kelle teenistuses asjaomased isikud t&ouml;&ouml;tasid. </eesti>
